    <svcproc id="s26510.2.13" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Manifold Absolute Pressure (MAP) Sensor</title>
        <figure id="e3001113" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ09/J09015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>MAP sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The MAP sensor, a variable capacitance sensor, measures intake manifold boost pressure.</para>
        <para>The MAP signal is monitored by the ECM for BCS, EGR valve, and engine fueling calculations.</para>
        <para>The MAP sensor is installed in the right front top of the intake manifold next to the air inlet elbow.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
